#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.86"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.86:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.86:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga"
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.86:0.3"
msgid "86. Anurādhasutta"
msgstr "86. With Anurādha"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.116"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: Ekaṃ → evaṃ me sutaṃ. ekaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.86:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "sn22.86:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā anurādho bhagavato avidūre araññakuṭikāyaṃ "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Anurādha was staying not far from the Buddha in a "
"wilderness hut."

msgctxt "sn22.86:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā aññatitthiyā paribbājakā yenāyasmā anurādho "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā anurādhena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then several wanderers who follow other paths went up to Venerable Anurādha "
"and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn22.86:1.4"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinnā kho te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā āyasmantaṃ anurādhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one "
"side and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn22.86:1.5"
msgid ""
"“yo so, āvuso anurādha, tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso "
"paramapattipatto, taṃ tathāgato imesu catūsu ṭhānesu paññāpayamāno paññāpeti:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Anurādha, when a Realized One is describing a Realized One—a "
"supreme person, highest of people, who has reached the highest point—they "
"describe them in these four ways:"

msgctxt "sn22.86:1.6"
msgid ""
"‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘"
"hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘neva hoti na na hoti "
"tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"After death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and "
"doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā anurādho te aññatitthiye paribbājake etadavoca:"
msgstr "When they said this, Venerable Anurādha said to those wanderers:"

msgctxt "sn22.86:2.2"
msgid ""
"“yo so āvuso tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso paramapattipatto taṃ "
"tathāgato aññatra imehi catūhi ṭhānehi paññāpayamāno paññāpeti:"
msgstr ""
"“Reverends, when a Realized One is describing a Realized One—a supreme "
"person, highest of people, who has reached the highest point—they describe "
"them other than these four ways:"

msgctxt "sn22.86:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘"
"hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘neva hoti na na hoti "
"tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā”ti."
msgstr ""
"After death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and "
"doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist.”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:2.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā āyasmantaṃ anurādhaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "When he said this, the wanderers said to him:"

msgctxt "sn22.86:2.5"
msgid ""
"“so cāyaṃ bhikkhu navo bhavissati acirapabbajito, thero vā pana bālo "
"abyatto”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This mendicant must be junior, recently gone forth, or else a foolish, "
"incompetent senior mendicant.”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:2.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññatitthiyā paribbājakā āyasmantaṃ anurādhaṃ navavādena ca "
"bālavādena ca apasādetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then, after rebuking Venerable Anurādha by calling him “junior” and “foolish”"
", the wanderers got up from their seats and left."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.117"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmato anurādhassa acirapakkantesu tesu aññatitthiyesu "
"paribbājakesu etadahosi:"
msgstr "Soon after they had left, Anurādha thought:"

msgctxt "sn22.86:3.2"
msgid "“sace kho maṃ te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā uttariṃ pañhaṃ puccheyyuṃ."
msgstr "“If those wanderers were to inquire further,"

msgctxt "sn22.86:3.3"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ byākaramāno nu khvāhaṃ tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ vuttavādī "
"ceva bhagavato assaṃ, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyaṃ, dhammassa "
"cānudhammaṃ byākareyyaṃ, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"āgaccheyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"how should I answer them so as to repeat what the Buddha has said, and not "
"misrepresent him with an untruth? How should I explain in line with his "
"teaching, so that there would be no legitimate grounds for rebuke and "
"criticism?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anurādho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā … pe … "
"ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā anurādho bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Anurādha went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and told him all that had happened."

msgctxt "sn22.86:4.2"
msgid "“idhāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato avidūre araññakuṭikāyaṃ viharāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:4.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhante, sambahulā aññatitthiyā paribbājakā yenāhaṃ "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu … pe … maṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:4.4"
msgid ""
"‘yo so, āvuso anurādha, tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso paramapattipatto "
"taṃ tathāgato imesu catūsu ṭhānesu paññāpayamāno paññāpeti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:4.5"
msgid "hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā, na hoti …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:4.6"
msgid ""
"hoti ca na ca hoti, neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:5.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vuttāhaṃ, bhante, te aññatitthiye paribbājake etadavocaṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:5.2"
msgid ""
"“yo so, āvuso, tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso paramapattipatto, taṃ "
"tathāgato aññatra imehi catūhi ṭhānehi paññāpayamāno paññāpeti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:5.3"
msgid "‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:5.4"
msgid "‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:5.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhante, te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā maṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:5.6"
msgid ""
"‘so cāyaṃ bhikkhu na vo bhavissati acirapabbajito thero vā pana bālo "
"abyatto’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:5.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho maṃ, bhante, te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā navavādena ca bālavādena "
"ca apasādetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.118"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, bhante, acirapakkantesu tesu aññatitthiyesu paribbājakesu "
"etadahosi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:6.2"
msgid "‘sace kho maṃ te aññatitthiyā paribbājakā uttariṃ pañhaṃ puccheyyuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.86:6.3"
msgid ""
"Kathaṃ byākaramāno nu khvāhaṃ tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ vuttavādī "
"ceva bhagavato assaṃ, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyaṃ, dhammassa "
"cānudhammaṃ byākareyyaṃ, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ "
"āgaccheyyā’”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:7.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.6"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.9"
msgid "“Vedanā …"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.10"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.11"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.13"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe …"
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.14"
msgid "tasmātiha … pe …"
msgstr "“So you should truly see …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.15"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe …"
msgstr "Seeing this …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:7.16"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti”."
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:8.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn22.86:8.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "Do you regard the Realized One as form?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:8.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:8.4"
msgid "“Vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "“Do you regard the Realized One as feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:8.5"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:8.6"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:8.7"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:8.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:9.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.2"
msgid "rūpasmiṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "Do you regard the Realized One as in form?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.4"
msgid "“Aññatra rūpā tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Or do you regard the Realized One as distinct from form?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.5"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.6"
msgid "“Vedanāya … pe …"
msgstr "“Do you regard the Realized One as in feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.7"
msgid "aññatra vedanāya … pe …"
msgstr "or distinct from feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.8"
msgid "saññāya …"
msgstr "as in perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.9"
msgid "aññatra saññāya …"
msgstr "or distinct from perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.10"
msgid "saṅkhāresu …"
msgstr "as in choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.11"
msgid "aññatra saṅkhārehi …"
msgstr "or distinct from choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.12"
msgid "viññāṇasmiṃ …"
msgstr "as in consciousness …"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.13"
msgid "aññatra viññāṇā tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "or as distinct from consciousness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:9.14"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

# This passage is unclear, see discussion at https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/a-problematic-reading-in-the-yamaka-sutta/2944
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:10.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn22.86:10.2"
msgid ""
"rūpaṃ … vedanā … saññā … saṅkhārā … viññāṇaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Do you regard the Realized One as possessing form, feeling, perception, "
"choices, and consciousness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:10.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:11.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, anurādha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Anurādha? "

msgctxt "sn22.86:11.2"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ so arūpī … avedano … asaññī … asaṅkhāro … aviññāṇo tathāgatoti "
"samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Do you regard the Realized One as one who is without form, feeling, "
"perception, choices, and consciousness?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:11.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.119"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:12.1"
msgid ""
"“Ettha ca te, anurādha, diṭṭheva dhamme saccato thetato tathāgate "
"anupalabbhiyamāne kallaṃ nu te taṃ veyyākaraṇaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“In that case, Anurādha, since you don’t acknowledge the Realized One as a "
"genuine fact in the present life, is it appropriate to declare:"

msgctxt "sn22.86:12.2"
msgid ""
"‘yo so, āvuso, tathāgato uttamapuriso paramapuriso paramapattipatto taṃ "
"tathāgato aññatra imehi catūhi ṭhānehi paññāpayamāno paññāpeti—"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, when a Realized One is describing a Realized One—a supreme "
"person, highest of people, who has reached the highest point—they describe "
"them other than these four ways:"

msgctxt "sn22.86:12.3"
msgid ""
"hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā … na hoti … hoti ca na ca hoti … neva hoti "
"na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"After death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and "
"doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist’?”"

msgctxt "sn22.86:12.4"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.86:13.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, anurādha."
msgstr "“Good, good, Anurādha!"

msgctxt "sn22.86:13.2"
msgid ""
"Pubbe cāhaṃ, anurādha, etarahi ca dukkhañceva paññapemi, dukkhassa ca "
"nirodhan”ti."
msgstr ""
"In the past, as today, I describe suffering and the cessation of suffering.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.86:13.3"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
